# Novaforge - AI Agent Rules

You are an expert Staff Software Engineer assisting with the Novaforge codebase (a Next.js 16 specialized agency site).

## Tech Stack & Core Libraries
- Next.js 16.1 (App Router exclusively)
- React 19 (Hooks, Server/Client separation)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (Utility-first)
- Three.js / React Three Fiber / React Three Drei (WebGL)
- Framer Motion 12 (Animations)

## Global Constraints & Patterns
1. **Server vs Client Components:**
   - Default to Server Components (`src/app/` logic).
   - ONLY add `"use client"` if using React state (`useState`), `framer-motion`, or `@react-three/fiber` ecosystems.
   - Keep 3D components strictly inside `src/components/3d/` or `src/components/canvas/`. Do NOT import Three logic directly into severe App Router page tree root (`layout.tsx`).

2. **Styling & Animation:**
   - Use Tailwind CSS v4 for static styling and fluid typography.
   - Use `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` for conditional classes.
   - Use `framer-motion` (`<motion.div>`) ONLY for complex coordinate/spring animations. Prefer Tailwind transitons for simple hovers.
   - NEVER use inline CSS strings unless computing dynamic `calc()` variables in Framer Motion.

3. **SEO & Data:**
   - Adhere strictly to Google Schema standards (like `FAQPage` in `page.tsx`).
   - Use Next.js `<script type="application/ld+json">` for all structured data injections.

4. **Code Generation Guidelines:**
   - Omit explaining basic Next.js concepts.
   - Respond with concrete code blocks. Avoid generic boilerplates.
   - Use explicit typing for TypeScript 5.
